# Git workflow (user-global)

Pairs with `editors/vscode/user/instructions/git-workflow.instructions.md`.

## No auto tests

Never run tests unless user explicitly asks (`run tests`, `npm test`, etc.). Ask first if tests seem useful.

## No auto commit/push

Never `git commit` or `git push` without explicit request (`commit`, `push`, `acp`, etc.). `git add` only when preparing a user-requested commit. Ask if unclear.

## ACP (when requested)

1. `git status` + `git diff --stat`
2. `git add -A`
3. Conventional commit from diff
4. `git push` only if user asked push

When a **project profile** defines custom commit format (e.g. novus ACP), follow that profile's `git-workflow-project` or operator-context instructions instead.

## Destructive commands

No rm/drop/reset/overwrite without explicit approval. Describe effect first; prefer non-destructive alternatives.
